#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:2
msgid "Building a bootable ISO image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:5
msgid ""
"If you need to build images for a different platform, see [Cross compiling]"
"(https://github.com/nix-community/nixos-generators#user-content-cross-"
"compiling)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:8
msgid ""
"You may find that an official installation image lacks some hardware support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:10
msgid ""
"The solution is to create `myimage.nix` to point to the latest kernel using "
"the minimal installation ISO:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:12
msgid ""
"{ pkgs, modulesPath, lib, ... }: {\n"
"  imports = [\n"
"    \"${modulesPath}/installer/cd-dvd/installation-cd-minimal.nix\"\n"
"  ];\n"
"\n"
"  # use the latest Linux kernel\n"
"  boot.kernelPackages = pkgs.linuxPackages_latest;\n"
"\n"
"  # Needed for https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/issues/58959\n"
"  boot.supportedFilesystems = lib.mkForce [ \"btrfs\" \"reiserfs\" \"vfat\" "
"\"f2fs\" \"xfs\" \"ntfs\" \"cifs\" ];\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:26
msgid "Generate an ISO with the above configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:28
msgid ""
"$ NIX_PATH=nixpkgs=https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/"
"archive/74e2faf5965a12e8fa5cff799b1b19c6cd26b0e3.tar.gz nix-shell -p nixos-"
"generators --run \"nixos-generate --format iso --configuration ./myimage.nix "
"-o result\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:32
msgid ""
"Copy the new image to your USB stick by replacing `sdX` with the name of "
"your device:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:34
msgid ""
"$ dd if=result/iso/*.iso of=/dev/sdX status=progress\n"
"$ sync\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:39
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:41
msgid ""
"Take a look at this [list of formats that the generators support](https://"
"github.com/nix-community/nixos-generators#user-content-supported-formats) to "
"find your cloud provider or virtualization technology."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-bootable-iso-image.md:42
msgid ""
"Take a look at the [alternative guide to create a NixOS live CD](https://"
"wiki.nixos.org/wiki/Creating_a_NixOS_live_CD)"
msgstr ""
